
            Video
            Madagascar women jailed for crimes male relatives are accused of
            Women in Madagascar say they are being jailed for crimes their male relatives are accused of.100 Women has had access to Madagascan prisons to speak to women who have been detained for months – and sometimes years – told they were "accomplices" or should have known what their husbands, brothers or sons were doing.BBC 100 Women names 100 influential and inspirational women around the world every year and shares their stories. Find us on Facebook, Instagram and Twitter and use #100Women.  
                
                        30 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
